{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782526100354,"sessionID":"ses_0f92f39d9ffeCt7pbKbzBwZvJW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wmdaiYbAiAEEMPh7DdzUiUIq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-source-walkthrough.md","limit":500},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-source-walkthrough.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Foodike Source Walkthrough\n2: \n3: ## Scope\n4: \n5: - Session type: source walkthrough before translation planning.\n6: - Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n7: - Target project for later phases: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n8: - Evidence sources used first: generated Kotlin/Android analysis under `translation-inputs/`, then direct source inspection where behavior needed confirmation.\n9: - Static-analysis caution: generated feature rows currently over-report file/storage/media/permission capabilities across many files; this walkthrough corrects those assumptions with direct code evidence.\n10: \n11: ## Current Baseline\n12: \n13: - App architecture: single Android app module using Jetpack Compose, Hilt DI, ViewModel state, Kotlin coroutines, Navigation Compose, and DataStore preferences.\n14: - Functional surface detected: onboarding, login, home feed, restaurant detail, cart, history/favourites, profile/logout, splash routing.\n15: - Data sources detected so far: static in-app fake catalog data plus DataStore-backed login/session flag.\n16: - Source tests detected: placeholder Android instrumented test and placeholder unit test only.\n17: - Source entry points detected so far:\n18:   - `app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`\n19:   - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/FoodikeApp.kt`\n20:   - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt`\n21:   - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt`\n22: \n23: ## High-Level Behavior Summary\n24: \n25: - Splash/startup chooses initial route from persisted login state.\n26: - Onboarding is a 3-page pager that advances to login.\n27: - Login screen collects email/password, exposes social-login buttons as presentational affordances, persists login state on success, and clears back stack to home.\n28: - Home screen renders ads, recommended foods, favourite restaurants, restaurant list, top/profile access, and navigates to details.\n29: - Restaurant detail screen renders selected restaurant metadata and menu sections, tracks liked state and expansion toggles in view-model state, and can navigate to cart.\n30: - Cart screen renders chosen restaurant delivery info, editable item quantities, coupon input, bill section, and bottom action.\n31: - History screen uses tabs/pager to show history placeholder content and favourites list with navigation back to details.\n32: - Profile screen shows static profile/help rows and logout action that clears login state and returns to onboarding.\n33: \n34: ## Architecture Clusters To Preserve In Planning\n35: \n36: - App shell and startup: application class, manifest, splash routing, main activity.\n37: - Navigation/state shell: route model, nav graph, bottom bar state, start-destination routing.\n38: - Domain models: advertisement, food item, restaurant, menu item, cart item.\n39: - Repository/data services: fake catalog repository, in-memory user-data repository, DataStore login repository.\n40: - Feature view models/state/events: login, home, details, cart, history, profile, splash.\n41: - UI feature pages: onboarding, login, home, details, cart, history, profile.\n42: - Reusable composables/theme/resources: cards, text field, search, chips, icons, strings/colors/themes.\n43: \n44: ## Analysis Gaps Already Confirmed\n45: \n46: - Generated coverage and capability files mark many files as file/media/permission/platform integrations, but direct inspection queue indicates the app is primarily static/demo data with no real file picker, MediaStore, runtime permission flow, notifications, widgets, or external sharing implementation.\n47: - Platform capability rows will need narrowing to actual capabilities such as Compose-style navigation, splash behavior, persisted login preference, and standard image/resource rendering.\n48: \n49: ## File-By-File Walkthrough\n50: \n51: This section is being expanded during the walkthrough. Each source code and behavior-carrying resource/config file will be listed with path, role, key types/functions, state/data behavior, side effects, dependency/resource evidence, and migration notes.\n\n(End of file - total 51 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Foodike Source Walkthrough\n\n## Scope\n\n- Session type: source walkthrough before translation planning.\n- Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n- Target project for later phases: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n- Evidence sources used first: generated Kotlin/Android analysis under `translation-inputs/`, then direct source inspection where behavior needed confirmation.\n- Static-analysis caution: generated feature rows currently over-report file/storage/media/permission capabilities across many files; this walkthrough corrects those assumptions with direct code evidence.\n\n## Current Baseline\n\n- App architecture: single Android app module using Jetpack Compose, Hilt DI, ViewModel state, Kotlin coroutines, Navigation Compose, and DataStore preferences.\n- Functional surface detected: onboarding, login, home feed, restaurant detail, cart, history/favourites, profile/logout, splash routing.\n- Data sources detected so far: static in-app fake catalog data plus DataStore-backed login/session flag.\n- Source tests detected: placeholder Android instrumented test and placeholder unit test only.\n- Source entry points detected so far:\n  - `app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`\n  - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/FoodikeApp.kt`\n  - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/MainActivity.kt`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\agent-source-walkthrough.md","time":{"start":1782526100349,"end":1782526100354}},"id":"prt_f06d5c366001ki0bhc081AQT6f","sessionID":"ses_0f92f39d9ffeCt7pbKbzBwZvJW","messageID":"msg_f06d58e2500148KZVNjxRYV2Kv"}}
